I usually go out of my way to be nice to people and help people.  Forget it now.  This one cleric has ruined my day, and I don't think I'm going to do jack for any stranger for some time to come.<br>
<br>
I died in EW today on the Kael ramp (deathsquad got me - I can usually evade them - but I've spent now 2 weeks running hunting Tanik, so odds are on me dying at some point).  I lost L52 on this death by a healthy margin.  Guild clerics aren't on yet, won't be until the timer expires most likely.  Don't see any in zone.  Spent a half-hour looking around for one, and getting my semi-bugged corpse dragged over to the zone.  None to be found.<br>
<br>
Then a cleric pops into zone, L51.  I sent a tell offering her 100p for a rez near Kael entrance.  Her reply was &quot;sorry, my group is in a hurry to get to GD&quot;.  Fine, I'm a little miffed at losing the only cleric I had seen, but hey, sometimes it's just out of the way for you, so I don't reply.<br>
<br>
10 minutes later - I'm at the Kael zone edge in EW - and the Cleric shows up with her group.  Don't ask me why she's there, since she was supposedly on the way to GD in a hurry 10 minutes before.  So I send her another tell &quot;It's an easy 100p, my corpse is right next to you&quot; - and then her and the group promptly zone into Kael and head out for god knows where (anywhere but GD).<br>
<br>
So the conversation continues:<br>
<br>
me - &quot;Bah - you were right here - I know one person I'm charging for ports from now on&quot;<br>
her - &quot;Sorry hun, I would, but we're in a hurry to get to a guild event&quot;<br>
me - &quot;My body was right next to you, it takes no time at all to cast rez&quot;<br>
her - &quot;My guildleader is in a rush, I had to go with my group&quot;<br>
me - &quot;Reconsider your guild if the leader can't see the logic in stopping for 1 minute to rez someone who's right there, for PR sake if not kindness&quot;<br>
<br>
(all paraphrased, not like I log my damn conversations)<br>
<br>
Like the spawns wouldn't have waited for them?  Like she wouldn't have stopped and walked the same few feet out of the way to pick 100p off the ground?  GRRRRRRRRRRRRR<br>
<br>
F-k her.  If she ever asks me for a port we're taking a ride to Hate together.  I don't mind mentioning her name for whoever on TP reads these threads.  Zariabeth.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I guess I'm hanging on the various boards all day until my clerics come on, I don't want to run out my timer and run up my frustration continuing my search for a nice cleric.<br>
 <p><BR>Cabot Coriolis of Tholuxe Paells<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 1:30:54 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: f-ing clerics</span><hr size=1> Cabot, no offence to you but it really, really is a pain in the ass to res people.  Yes, it's nice but it really is a pain in the ass. <br>
